From: Anders da Silva Rytter Hansen <andersrh@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 13:39:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] meson: use string prefix for Meson < 1.3 compatibility

Meson versions prior to 1.3 expect the `prefix` argument passed to
`compiler.has_member()` to be a single string rather than a list of
strings.  Enterprise Linux 9 still ships Meson 0.63, causing the build
system to error out when presented with the list form introduced
upstream.  Convert the includes to a multiline string so the check works
with both older and newer Meson releases.
---
 include/meson.build | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/include/meson.build
+++ b/include/meson.build
@@
-  cc.has_member(
-     'struct sockaddr_in', 'sin_len',
-     prefix: ['#include <sys/types.h>', '#include <sys/socket.h>',
-              '#include <netinet/in.h>'],
-  )  ? '1' : false,
+  cc.has_member(
+     'struct sockaddr_in', 'sin_len',
+     prefix: '''#include <sys/types.h>
+#include <sys/socket.h>
+#include <netinet/in.h>''',
+  )  ? '1' : false,
   description: 'Define to 1 if `struct sockaddr_in' has a `sin_len' member',
 )
